12/11/2010
STRASBOURG, France -- Turkey took over chairmanship of the Committee of Ministers of the Council of Europe (CoE) from Macedonia at a ceremony in Strasbourg, France, on Wednesday (November 10th).
During it, Foreign Minister Ahmet Davutoglu stressed his country would work to improve the organisation's role, visibility and efficiency, both in Europe and worldwide.
Turkey will hold the chairmanship for a period of six months, until May 11th 2011.
During this period, Davutoglu will serve as president of the Committee of Ministers of the CoE.
(Anadolu news agency, World Bulletin - 11/11/10)
